This one isn't fully necessary but it's there if you need to square-up on a black line without PVC being present
It's also pretty short
It's kinda like line follow
We need 2 light sensors for this, evenly spaced from the center
Also when you define the port numbers the format is "#define X Y" X is name and Y is value
Try to make the sensor ports the same number as the wheel ports you use
Ok lets go

#define RIGHT |INSERT RIGHT SENSOR PORT|
#define LEFT |INSERT LEFT SENSOR PORT|

void line_square_up(){
  while(analog(RIGHT) < 1700 || analog(LEFT) < 1700){
    if(analog(RIGHT) < 1700){
      mav(RIGHT, 500);
    }
      else {
      mav(RIGHT, -250);
    }
    if(analog(LEFT) < 1700){
      mav(LEFT, 500);
    }
    else {
      mav(LEFT, -250);
    }
  mav(LEFT, 0);
  mav(RIGHT, 0);
  msleep(50);

